  "StockRole": "Brawler",
  "YangsThoughts": "The Seishin came out of the post-Jihad salvage boom, when pirates across the Periphery suddenly had access to Word of Blake hardware they had no business owning and the ambition to do something creative with it. The design caught on in the Tortuga Dominions and built a nasty reputation, because a mech optimized for taking prisoners and capturing hardware intact is genuinely harder to deal with than one that just wants to kill you. The Shield and Retractable Blade tell you exactly what happens if the taser does not land.",
